# dq.nim
## Compilation
```sh
nim c -r -d:fmu dq.nim
```

## Testing

```sh
../fmuCheck.linux64 -h 0.2 -s 5 -f -l 6 -e dq.log dq.fmu
```
This creates the log file: [dq.log](https://github.com/mantielero/fmu.nim/blob/main/examples/dq/dq.log).

It also displays the following results:
